      "id": "9a9944e62c0359eb",
      "text": "and p. 108n69: In his contribution to this volume, for example, [[Dirk Baecker]] shows that, contrary to the first intuition, the violence of terrorism should not be understood intentionally, but rather functionally, namely as a moment of the political system, and to what extent it should be read as an indication of underlying processes of change in the communicative structure of world society."
